Within 12 hours after the onset of illness, the sensitivity and specificity were 100% and 97.8%, respectively (n = 82). Although the sensitivity did not decrease within 48 hours, the specificity gradually decreased with time, as follows: within 12 hours, 97.8%; 13–24 hours, 88.8%; 25–48 hours, 81.8% (
 Table 3
 ). After 48 hours, both the sensitivity and specificity decreased. However, there was no statistically significant difference in the sensitivity and specificity between the patients tested within 12 hours after the onset of illness and those tested at more than 48 hours after the onset of illness.
